4 in baseball|Asian Games]]\n[[Category:International baseball competitions hosted by Japan|1994 Asian Games]]\n", "name_user": "Jonesey95", "label": "safe", "comment": "FixLintererrors usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baseball_at_the_1994_Asian_Games"}
{"title_page": "Aloha (Hawaii Five-0)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television episode\n| RTitle         = \"Aloha\"\n| series         = [[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]\n| image          = H50FinalePart2.png\n| image_size     = <!-- raw number. \"px\" not required. -->\n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| season         = 10\n| series_no      = \n| episode        = 22\n| multi_episodes = \n| director       = [[Duane Clark]]\n| writer         = \n| story          = [[Peter M. Lenkov]]\n| teleplay       = David Wolkove & [[Matt Wheeler]]\n| based_on       = \n| narrator       = \n| presenter      = \n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Peter M. Lenkov]]\n* David Wolkove\n* [[Alex Kurtzman]]\n* [[Roberto Orci]]\n* [[Matt Wheeler]]\n}}\n| music          = \"''All for One Ohana''\" by [[Five for Fighting]]\n| photographer   = \n| editor         = \n| production     = 1022\n| airdate        = {{Start date|2020|04|03}}\n| length         = \n| awards         = \n| guests         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Lance Gross]] as Lincoln Cole\n* [[Eugenia Yuan]] as Daiyu Mei\n* [[William Sadler (actor)|William Sadler]] as John McGarrett\n* [[James Marsters]] as Victor Hesse\n* [[Mark Dacascos]] as [[Wo Fat]]\n* Michael Hagiwara as Ryo\n* [[Amelia Cooke]] as Lead Doctor\n* Robert Law as Nurse\n* Geraldo Morales as Airline Passenger\n}}\n| prev           = [[A 'ohe ia e loa'a aku, he ulua kapapa no ka moana]]\n| next           =\n| season_article = Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series, season 10)\n| episode_list   = List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) episodes\n}}\n\n{{Redirect|Hawaii Five-0 finale|finale of the 1968 TV series|Hawaii Five-O (1968 TV series, season 12)#ep279}}\n\n\"'''Aloha'''\" ([[Hawaiian language|Hawaiian for]]: \"'''Goodbye'''\") is the second part, of the two-part [[Series finale|series finale]] of [[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|''Hawaii Five-0'']]. It is also the twenty-second episode of the [[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series, season 10)|tenth season]]. It is set to air on April 3, 2020. The story for the episode was written by [[Peter M. Lenkov]], and the teleplay was written by David Wolkove and [[Matt Wheeler]]. The episode was directed by [[Duane Clark]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B9SKHD7gm7G/|title=Last #H50 callsheet. Scotch & Cigar time. 10 years. You went way too fast. Aloha.|last=Lenkov|first=Peter|author-link=Peter Lenkov|date=March 3, 2020|accessdate=March 3, 2020|work=[[Instagram]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--==Plot==\n-->\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn February 28, 2020, it was announced that ''Hawaii Five-0'' would conclude after the [[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series, season 10)|tenth season]] with a two-part series finale.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/hawaii-five-0-end-10-seasons-canceled-cbs-s-two-hour-series-finale-1202870780/|title=\u2018Hawaii Five-0\u2019 To End After 10 Seasons On CBS, Sets Two-Hour Series Finale|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> The episode's title was revealed to be \"Aloha\" in an [[instagram]] post by developer, [[showrunner]], and executive producer [[Peter M. Lenkov]] on March 3, 2020, when he also announced that it would be the final day of filming.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B9SKHD7gm7G/|title=Last #H50 callsheet. Scotch & Cigar time. 10 years. You went way too fast. Aloha.|last=Lenkov|first=Peter M.|author-link=Peter M. Lenkov|date=March 3, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|work=[[Instagram]]}}</ref> [[Five for Fighting]] recorded an acoustic version of All for One, a song by the same band made for [[Ina Paha|the one-hundredth episode]], and entitled it All for One Ohana.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241060503566209025|title=Actually a brand new acoustic version...We are calling it All For One Ohana|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|last=Ondrasik|first=John|author-link=John Ondrasik|user=johnondrasik}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241095831190564864|title=Here ya go fellow @HawaiiFive0CBS fans! Sneak Peak at All for One Ohana cover art. Shot and designed by @PLenkov's better half Audie Lenkov! (Ok the badge Idea was Peter's). What's everyone doing tonight? \ud83d\ude03||date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|last=Ondrasik|first=John|author-link=John Ondrasik|user=johnondrasik}}</ref> A cut version of the song was used in the episode's trailer, with the song originally set to release on streaming on platforms on March 20.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241037747504087042|title=The great \u2066@johnondrasik redid his masterful 100th ep song for our finale. I believe it\u2019ll be on iTunes any minute now... #H50 Series finale|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|last=Lenkov|first=Peter M.|author-link=Peter M. Lenkov|user=PLenkov}}</ref> The release date however, was pushed back and is currently set to be released by April 3.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241092575081025536|title=Maybe give fans a sneak at the cover art? Good consolation prize until the release?|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|last=Lenkov|first=Peter M.|author-link=Peter M. Lenkov|user=PLenkov}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nOn February 14, 2020 it was announced that [[Lance Gross]] would appear as Lincoln Cole.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/hawaii-five-o-lance-gross-cast-final-two-episodes-season-10-option-series-regular-1202860564/|title=\u2018Hawaii Five-O\u2019: Lance Gross Joins Cast As Potential Series Regular|date=February 14, 2020|work=Deadline}}</ref> On February 28, 2020 it was announced that [[James Marsters]] would return as Victor Hesse, [[William Sadler (actor)|William Sadler]] as John McGarrett, and [[Mark Dacascos]] as [[Wo Fat]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/hawaii-five-0-to-end-after-10-seasons/|title=\u2018Hawaii Five-0\u2019 to End After 10 Seasons|last=Baysinger|first=Tim|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020|work=[[The Wrap]]}}</ref> [[Will Yun Lee]], who recurred in the series as Sang Min, revealed that due to his tight schedule he was not able to appear in the finale despite the heavy attempt.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241192379748454401|title=@PLenkov was truly amazing in trying to make the schedule work. I just had a tight schedule that wouldn\u2019t allow it. But @HawaiiFive0CBS will truly be one of the most memorable experiences and characters I had the opp to play #ForeverSangMin \ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffd\ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffd\ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffdRed heart #H50|last=Lee|first=Will Yun|author-link=Will Yun Lee|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|user=WillYunLee}}</ref>\n\n===Release===\nThe episode was originally set to be part of a two-hour series finale, however due to the cancellation of the [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament]], the first part was moved up a week (along with the cornavirus), and this episode will now air an hour earlier (its regular timeslot) on April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/03/13/hawaii-five-0-series-finale-date-cbs-season-10/|title=CBS Unveils March Madness Replacement Plan, Hawaii Five-0's Two-Hour Series Finale to Be Split\n|date=March 13, 2020|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|work=[[TVLine]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--==Reception==\n===Viewing figures===\n\n===Critical response===\n\n\n-->==Part 1==\n{{main|A 'ohe ia e loa'a aku, he ulua kapapa no ka moana}}\nThe first part of the two-part finale, titled \"''A 'ohe ia e loa'a aku, he ulua kapapa no ka moana''\", aired on March 27, 2020.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) episodes]]\n*[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series, season 10)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.cbs.com/shows/hawaii_five_0/|Hawaii Five-0 official website on CBS}}\n\n{{Hawaii Five-O}}\n\n[[Category:2020 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) episodes]]\n[[Category:American television series finales]]\n", "text_old": 