hat due to his tight schedule he was not able to appear in the finale despite the heavy attempt.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1241192379748454401|title=@PLenkov was truly amazing in trying to make the schedule work. I just had a tight schedule that wouldn\u2019t allow it. But @HawaiiFive0CBS will truly be one of the most memorable experiences and characters I had the opp to play #ForeverSangMin \ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffd\ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffd\ud83e\udd19\ud83c\udffdRed heart #H50|last=Lee|first=Will Yun|author-link=Will Yun Lee|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|user=WillYunLee}}</ref>\n\n===Release===\nThe episode was originally set to be part of a two-hour series finale, however due to the cancellation of the [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament]], the first part was moved up a week, and this episode will now air an hour earlier (its regular timeslot) on April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/03/13/hawaii-five-0-series-finale-date-cbs-season-10/|title=CBS Unveils March Madness Replacement Plan, Hawaii Five-0's Two-Hour Series Finale to Be Split\n|date=March 13, 2020|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|work=[[TVLine]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--==Reception==\n===Viewing figures===\n\n===Critical response===\n\n\n-->==Part 1==\n{{main|A 'ohe ia e loa'a aku, he ulua kapapa no ka moana}}\nThe first part of the two-part finale, titled \"''A 'ohe ia e loa'a aku, he ulua kapapa no ka moana''\", aired on March 27, 2020.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) episodes]]\n*[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series, season 10)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.cbs.com/shows/hawaii_five_0/|Hawaii Five-0 official website on CBS}}\n\n{{Hawaii Five-O}}\n\n[[Category:2020 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) episodes]]\n[[Category:American television series finales]]\n", "name_user": "74.98.249.253", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.